    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>3-1-185</b>\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"bafd7322c6e97d25b6299b5d6fe8920b\">No</span> English term\n</p><p>Term describing equality of loudness of the auditory sensations produced by several sounds or noises of different character, under given conditions.\n</p><p>Reference: <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0d61f8370cad1d412f80b84d143e1257\">C</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"3a3ea00cfc35332cedf6e5e9a32e94da\">E</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"800618943025315f869e4e1f09471012\">F</span>.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"bafd7322c6e97d25b6299b5d6fe8920b\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Number of cells\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0d61f8370ca